::: slide layout=cover
title: SecondBrain
subtitle: Business Brief — Build in Public
footer: Brandon Situ · April 2026
:::

::: slide layout=section_divider
title: Opportunity
:::

::: slide layout=content
title: Why now
body: |
  Personal AI infrastructure is moving from "novelty" to "table stakes" for
  knowledge workers. The window for credible practitioner storytelling is open
  but closing fast as Notion AI and Anthropic Memory normalize the category.

  - Anthropic ships Claude Memory beta (March 2026)
  - Cursor launches workspace-scoped agents
  - Notion AI hits 10M paid seats
notes: |
  Lead with Anthropic + Cursor as signal of mainstream momentum. Notion's
  scale is the proof point. Don't bury the "passive dataset" angle - that's
  the differentiator.
:::

::: slide layout=section_divider
title: Audience
:::

::: slide layout=two_column
title: Who this campaign serves
left_title: Builder-curious professionals
left_body: |
  - Building side projects with AI tools after 9-5
  - Treat personal AI infra as table stakes
  - Read Stratechery, listen to Lenny's Podcast
  - Will share posts that make them look smart in their group chat
right_title: Consultant-builders
right_body: |
  - Senior enterprise leaders shipping internal AI tools
  - Want to understand "personal AI infrastructure" in practice
  - Often DM after seeing build-in-public posts
  - Inbound channel for advisory engagements
:::

::: slide layout=section_divider
title: Business Goal
:::

::: slide layout=content
title: What success looks like
body: |
  Inbound signal - DMs from enterprise leaders asking variants of "can you
  help us build something like this for our team?"

  Binary success criteria:
  - 2+ inbound DMs from director-or-above titles within 30 days of Post 1
  - 1+ booked discovery call from inbound traffic
  - GitHub blueprint repo passes 100 stars within 60 days
notes: |
  Reviewer cares about goal #1 most. #2 is the conversion signal. #3 is the
  vanity metric Brandon won't optimize for but stakeholders ask about.
:::

::: slide layout=section_divider
title: Risks
:::

::: slide layout=content
title: What could break this
body: |
  - **Audience read-through**: enterprise leaders may bounce off the
    Westworld/Rehoboam reference as too nerdy. Mitigation: lead the post
    with the practical infrastructure, save the narrative payoff for the end.
  - **Engagement gating risk**: Post 2 (the GitHub drop) only ships if Post 1
    earns >50 thoughtful comments. If it underperforms, we burn the series.
  - **Privacy backlash**: Screenpipe captures screen content. The "I'm
    building a dataset of myself" framing invites privacy critics. Address
    head-on in Post 3 (local models).
:::

::: slide layout=callout_quote
quote: "I'm not building a note-taker. I'm building a passive dataset of myself."
attribution: Brandon Situ
:::

::: slide layout=section_divider
title: Constraints
:::

::: slide layout=content
title: What can't change
body: |
  - **Timeline**: Post 1 ships week of April 28. Sundays are the publishing
    cadence - moving the date breaks the rhythm.
  - **Channel**: LinkedIn first. Carousel format. GitHub repo as the asset
    drop on Post 2.
  - **Voice**: Practitioner POV. No "thought leader" framing. No banned
    words from voice.md (notably: "leverage", "synergy", "thought leader").
  - **Series scope**: 2 minimum, 3 if Post 2 hits engagement target. Hard
    cap at 4 - the system goes from interesting to indulgent past that.
:::

::: slide layout=closing
title: Decision needed
body: |
  Approve the campaign brief direction by Wednesday April 22 to keep the
  April 28 publish date. If you have edits to the audience targeting or the
  GitHub-drop trigger, those are easier to adjust this week than next.
cta: Reply by Tuesday with your steer or any redlines.
:::
